2 Ways to Implement JavaScript :

.Inpage JavaScript
.External JavaScript

1. Inpage JavaScript

<html>

    <head>

        <script>

        </script>

    </head>

    <body>

        <h1>Yahoo Baba</h1>
        
        <script>

        </script>

    </body>

</html>

2. External JavaScript

Whenever we create a JavaScript file, we always add 'Js' at the end.

Like this:

filename.js
myScript.js
script.js

In code:

<head>

    <script src="Script.js"></script>

</head>

2 Type of comments:

.Single Line Comment
.Multiple Line Comment

Single Line Comment:

<script>

    Document.write("Hello World");//Here Is Single Line Comment

</script>

Multiple Line Comment:

<script>

    Document.write("Hello World");/*Here Is Multiple Line Comment
    Which Is Written In Multiple Lines*/
    
</script>

Variables:

document.write("Hello World");
document.write("Hello World");
document.write("Hello World");

Use of Variables:

A = Yahoo Baba

document.write(A);
document.write(A);
document.write(A);

Three Types of Comments:

. Var
. Let
. Const 

How to use Variables:

<script>
    
  var x = "Yahoo Baba"; //var x is Variable Name and "Yahoo Baba" is Variable Value

</script>